'''Exequiel Alejandro Palacios''' ({{IPA|es|ekseˈkjel paˈla.sjos}}; born 5 October 1998) is an Argentine professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for {{German football updater|BaLeverk}} club [[Bayer 04 Leverkusen|Bayer Leverkusen]] and the [[Argentina national football team|Argentina national team]].

==Club career==
===River Plate===
Palacios is a youth exponent from [[Club Atlético River Plate]]. He made his [[Argentine Primera División|league debut]] on 8 November 2015 against [[Newell's Old Boys]].<ref name="soccerway2">{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2015/11/08/argentina/primera-division/club-atletico-river-plate/newell-s-old-boys/1978582/|title=River Plate vs. Newell's Old Boys – 8 November 2015 – Soccerway|publisher=soccerway.com|access-date=2 December 2015}}</ref>

On 9 December 2018 Palacios won [[2018 Copa Libertadores]] with River Plate. He played 11 matches including [[2018 Copa Libertadores finals|the finals]] against rivals [[Boca Juniors]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Lowe |first1=Sid |title=River Plate claim Copa Libertadores against 10-man Boca with Quintero goal |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2018/dec/09/copa-libertadores-final-river-plate-boca-juniors-match-report |website=The Guardian |publisher=The Guardian |access-date=15 April 2024}}</ref>

Palacios was part of [[2018 South American Footballer of the Year|2018 South American Team of the Year]].

Palacios made his final appearance for his boyhood club in the final of the [[2018–19 Copa Argentina|Copa Argentina]] on 13 December 2019, playing 79 minutes of a 3–0 victory over [[Central Córdoba de Santiago del Estero|Central Córdoba]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.copaargentina.org/es/partido/3274_Central-Cordoba-SdE-vs-River.html|title=Central Córdoba (SdE) 0-3 River|website=Copa Argentina|date=13 December 2019|access-date=3 January 2020|language=es}}</ref>

===Bayer Leverkusen===
On 16 December 2019, [[Bayer 04 Leverkusen|Bayer Leverkusen]] announced that Palacios would join the club on 1 January 2020, signing a five-and-a-half-year deal.<ref>{{cite web |title=Bayer 04 sign Exequiel Palacios |url=https://www.bayer04.de/en-us/news/bayer04/bayer-04-sign-exequiel-palacios |website=Bayer Leverkusen |access-date=16 December 2019 |date=16 December 2019}}</ref>

On 14 April 2024, Bayer Leverkusen won [[2023–24 Bundesliga]] and Palacios was a member of the team.<ref>{{cite web |title=Exequiel Palacios – Centrocampista Bayer 04 |url=https://www.bayer04.de/en-us/player/werkself/bayer-04-leverkusen/exequiel-palacios#profile |website=Exequiel Palacios – Midfield Bayer 04 |access-date=15 April 2024}}</ref>

==International career==
Palacios made his international debut for [[Argentina national football team|Argentina]] on 8 September 2018 in a 3–0 international friendly against the [[Guatemala national football team]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://us.soccerway.com/matches/2018/09/08/world/friendlies/argentina/guatemala/2805437/|title = Argentina vs. Guatemala - 8 September 2018 - Soccerway}}</ref>

On 12 November 2020, Palacios fractured a bone in his spine during a 1–1 draw with [[Paraguay national football team|Paraguay]] in a [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification (CONMEBOL)|World Cup qualifier]] and was expected be out for three months. Palacios sustained the injury in an aerial duel with [[Angel Romero (footballer)|Angel Romero]] in the first half of the contest at [[La Bombonera]] and was replaced by [[Giovani Lo Celso]], who took the corner from which [[Nicolás González (footballer, born 1998)|Nicolas Gonzalez]] headed home Argentina's equaliser.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/fifa-world-cup-qualifying-conmebol/story/4234050/argentinas-palacios-suffers-fractured-spine-following-aerial-challenge|title=Argentina's Palacios suffers fractured spine following aerial challenge|website=ESPN|date=13 November 2020|access-date=13 November 2020}}</ref>

On 10 July 2021, Palacios played as a second-half substitute in Argentina's 1–0 victory over [[Brazil national football team|Brazil]] in the [[2021 Copa América final|Copa América final]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/live/2021/jul/10/argentina-v-brazil-copa-america-final-live |title=Argentina 1–0 Brazil |publisher=The Guardian |date=11 July 2021 }}</ref> During the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]], Palacios featured in a 2–0 win over [[Mexico national football team|Mexico]] in the group stage phase, a 2–1 victory over [[Australia men's national soccer team|Australia]] in the round of 16, and a 3–0 win over [[Croatia national football team|Croatia]] in their semi-finals.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bayer04.de/en-us/news/bayer04/world-cup-winner-palacios-grateful-to-everybody-at-bayer-04 |title=World Cup winner Palacios: 'Grateful to everybody at Bayer 04' |publisher=Bayer 04 Leverkusen |date=3 January 2023 }}</ref>

In June 2024, Palacios was included in Lionel Scaloni's final 26-man Argentina squad for the [[2024 Copa América]].<ref>{{Cite news |date=15 June 2024 |title=Lionel Scaloni dio a conocer la lista de la Selección argentina para la Copa América 2024 |url=https://tn.com.ar/deportes/futbol/2024/06/15/lionel-scaloni-dio-a-conocer-la-lista-de-la-seleccion-argentina-para-la-copa-america-2024/?gad_source=1&gclid=CjwKCAjwqf20BhBwEiwAt7dtdeK13_I24H4iqEBua7UtmDLn6_x-FfDm-gzEseLS8vJCnOlmjC3PlBoCHEwQAvD_BwE |access-date=23 July 2024 |work=Todo Noticias}}</ref>

